---+ !!Wireless Network Service

*%RED%UKP does not offer a wireless network. We also don't support it. Check the setup documentation of HRZ and report to them if you encounter any issues.%ENDCOLOR%*

Wireless network access is possible using eduroam, a wireless network provides by the HRZ of TU Darmstadt. A special device wlan account is needed from 2023 on to use eduroam. For more information please refer to the [[https://www.hrz.tu-darmstadt.de/netz/netzzugang_internet/netz_datennetz_internet_wlan_1/index.en.jsp][HRZ documentation]]. To access UKP-internal services after connecting to the HRZ wireless network, you have to open a [[Services/ITBasic.VpnService][VPN connection]] to the UKP network.

Quicklinks and HowTos:
   * [[https://www.hrz.tu-darmstadt.de/media/hrz/responsive_design/support_und_anleitungen/anleitungen/infrastruktur/wlan_2/W-LAN_manuelle_Konfiguration-Linux.pdf][Manual Setup of eduroam on Linux]]
   * [[https://www.idm.tu-darmstadt.de/wlan/][Create WLAN login account]] in IDM System of TU Darmstadt - [[https://www.hrz.tu-darmstadt.de/media/hrz/responsive_design/support_und_anleitungen/anleitungen/infrastruktur/wlan_2/Anleitung_WLAN-Accounts_DE.en.pdf][instructions]]
   * [[https://www.hrz.tu-darmstadt.de/support_und_anleitungen/hrz_anleitungen/wlan_anleitungen/index.en.jsp][Use the configuration assistant tool - esp. on MAC!]]

Notes:
   * HRZ also offers the possibility to create temporary eduroam guest accounts. Follow the HRZ documentation link from above.
   * TM: Note that the instructions provided by HRZ say that you need to point your network configuration to a Deutsche Telekom certificate in PEM format.  This didn't work for me; I had to use the CRT version of the certificate.

